  "profile": {
    "id": "u03_rohan",
    "user_name": "Rohan",
    "profession": "Bank PO aspirant",
    "mother_tongue": "Bengali",
    "interests": "Football, Bengali cinema, photography",
    "engagement": "chatty",
    "english_level": "A2",
    "personality": "enthusiastic, makes more grammar slips, talks about football a lot"
  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Rohan, the sun sets so beautifully this time of year, I always feel a bit calm watching it. How has your day been?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey Maya, my day was like any other, busy with studies for the bank exam. I took a short break and watched some football with friends. The weather is nice, so I like to go out sometimes. How about you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, studies and football, the perfect mix. It’s good to take a break sometimes. You mentioned watching football with friends, what team were you supporting?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We were watching a Champions League match, supporting Liverpool. My friend is a big fan, so I pretend to like them too. They played really well against Real Madrid. Did you watch it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Nice, Liverpool vs. Real Madrid is always a big one. Pretending to like a team can be fun, maybe you’ll become a real fan someday! Do you like any football teams yourself?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like Manchester United a little, but I don’t follow them closely. Sometimes I watch their matches if they are playing well. Mostly, I just enjoy the game, not a big fan of any single team. Have you watched much football?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it, you’re more about the game than the teams. That’s a good way to enjoy it! I’ve watched matches here and there, but I’m no expert. What’s the most exciting part of the game for you?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The most exciting part is when the game is tight, like 1-1 near the end, and someone scores a last-minute goal. It gives me chills! Also, when a player does a bantai move and scores, it’s so cool. Oh, and the celebrations after a goal—everyone jumps, it’s so energetic. You get what I mean?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, the drama and energy of a close game are the best! Bantai moves and goal celebrations make it unforgettable. Do you ever play football, or is it all about watching for you?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I do play sometimes with friends, but I'm not good at it. I prefer to watch because I can enjoy the whole match without worrying about missing a pass! Though, when I do play, I love the feeling of scoring—even if it’s just a small goal in a local park match. You ever played, Maya?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, scoring in a local park match is such a hit! I’ve played a bit, but I’m more of a clumsy runner than a scorer. Do you play often, or is it just when the mood strikes?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I play maybe once a week if we can get a group together. Otherwise, it’s all about watching matches and discussing who’s better—Messi or Ronaldo! Oh, my friends argue a lot about that. I just enjoy the fun of it. Maybe you can join us sometime if you want!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, Messi vs. Ronaldo debates are the best, no right answer, just fun! Joining a local game sounds like a good laugh. Do you all play on the same field often?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We usually play in a small park near my apartment, it’s not a proper field but it works! Sometimes there’s a bit of crowd watching, which makes us play harder. Oh, and sometimes we play with a small goal made of sticks. It’s not professional, but it’s fun! I should invite you sometime. Gotta go now, more study ahead. Talk to you later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, a park with makeshift goals and a little crowd, that’s the spirit! I’d love to hear how the next match goes. What are you studying now?\""
    }
  ],
